68
00:05:53,978 --> 00:05:57,178
What on earth does the culprit want to say?

69
00:05:57,178 --> 00:05:59,078
It's that, that!

70
00:05:59,078 --> 00:06:01,178
A dog and balls.

71
00:06:01,178 --> 00:06:07,278
Hey. None of your stupid play on words again now.

72
00:06:07,278 --> 00:06:10,678
You can say whatever you like! I'm all ears.

73
00:06:10,678 --> 00:06:13,578
It could turn out to be a hint!

74
00:06:15,378 --> 00:06:19,078
No! It's stupid so I don't think so!

75
00:06:21,278 --> 00:06:24,278
Hey, you! Don't hold out on us! Say it!

76
00:06:24,278 --> 00:06:27,778
I won't ever say it!

77
00:06:32,078 --> 00:06:36,278
It's true that there are traces of the grass having burned.

78
00:06:36,278 --> 00:06:37,978
The rope that was tied by the edge of the cliff

79
00:06:37,978 --> 00:06:40,678
-had been cut too. -Besides...

80
00:06:42,278 --> 00:06:44,978
The sign has also been pulled out.

81
00:06:44,978 --> 00:06:47,778
The road sign that was beyond the forked road

82
00:06:47,778 --> 00:06:49,778
"Inubushi Residence" -was also knocked down.

83
00:06:49,778 --> 00:06:53,878
I see. If chased by a dog in the dark like this

84
00:06:53,878 --> 00:06:57,378
without a road sign or a rope,

85
00:06:57,378 --> 00:07:01,878
it would send anyone right over the cliff!

86
00:07:01,878 --> 00:07:08,178
The problem is the demon dog that attacked, right?

87
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:10,678
There's no such thing as a demon dog!

88
00:07:10,678 --> 00:07:12,878
This is a psychological trick!

89
00:07:12,878 --> 00:07:15,078
It's just being made to look as if

90
00:07:15,078 --> 00:07:19,078
a demon dog exists with the story of the cursed dog in the past

91
00:07:19,078 --> 00:07:21,478
and the fire footprints!

92
00:07:21,478 --> 00:07:25,078
Fluorescent paint was probably used on the dog to make it glow!

93
00:07:25,078 --> 00:07:28,578
-Fluorescent paint? -Yeah!

94
00:07:28,578 --> 00:07:31,178
Since something that usually isn't glowing was glowing,

95
00:07:31,178 --> 00:07:33,778
it gave the mistaken impression that something was burning!

96
00:07:33,778 --> 00:07:35,678
Then, what about the fire footprints?

97
00:07:35,678 --> 00:07:37,978
There was no smell of oil, was there?

98
00:07:37,978 --> 00:07:42,178
Maybe the fire was set by using a gas burner or something?

99
00:07:44,278 --> 00:07:45,778
What is it, Kazuha?

100
00:07:45,778 --> 00:07:47,978
It's going to take us a little mover time yet,

101
00:07:47,978 --> 00:07:51,578
so if you get sleepy, don't wait for us and...

102
00:07:51,578 --> 00:07:53,078
What?

103
00:07:53,778 --> 00:07:56,378
The demon dog appeared at the house?

104
00:07:58,378 --> 00:08:02,278
Really? Was the dog really burning?

105
00:08:02,278 --> 00:08:04,178
Yes.

106
00:08:04,178 --> 00:08:06,678
-Right, Ran? -Yes!

107
00:08:06,678 --> 00:08:09,478
It wasn't fluorescent paint or anything!

108
00:08:09,478 --> 00:08:11,778
Although the fire's gone already.

109
00:08:11,778 --> 00:08:15,278
There were fire footprints left where the dog went by.

110
00:08:15,278 --> 00:08:19,878
True. There are burnt remains just like we saw on the cliff.

111
00:08:19,878 --> 00:08:23,478
And, where did that dog come from?

112
00:08:23,478 --> 00:08:25,878
From over that side!

113
00:08:27,578 --> 00:08:30,478
These footprints are strange.

114
00:08:31,378 --> 00:08:34,478
See, judging from the space of the footsteps,

115
00:08:34,478 --> 00:08:36,878
there should be some around here too,

116
00:08:36,878 --> 00:08:39,378
but there's none here at all!

117
00:08:39,378 --> 00:08:42,078
Besides, the ground is messed up only over here.

118
00:08:42,078 --> 00:08:45,378
That's the place you fell, right, Kazuha?

119
00:08:51,278 --> 00:08:52,478
Yes...

120
00:08:52,478 --> 00:08:57,378
and when I fell, I smelled something strange.

121
00:08:57,378 --> 00:08:59,778
What do you mean strange?

122
00:08:59,778 --> 00:09:04,578
Like rotten onions or something. It had a pungent foul smell.

123
00:09:04,578 --> 00:09:06,378
Onions?

124
00:09:06,378 --> 00:09:10,578
Oh, and after we evacuated into the house,

125
00:09:10,578 --> 00:09:12,978
we came right out again and saw...

126
00:09:12,978 --> 00:09:16,078
It looked kind of alive.

127
00:09:16,078 --> 00:09:19,978
Of course! It attacked after all.

128
00:09:19,978 --> 00:09:25,578
Oh, no. Not the demon dog, but the burnt footprints.

129
00:09:25,578 --> 00:09:29,878
It seemed to be hopping around while making a clanking sound.

130
00:09:30,478 --> 00:09:32,378
You saw it too, didn't you, Kazuha?

131
00:09:32,378 --> 00:09:33,678
I did, I saw it!

132
00:09:33,678 --> 00:09:37,978
It looked as though the footprints had souls in them!

133
00:09:37,978 --> 00:09:40,578
It's surprising that you went outside again.

134
00:09:40,578 --> 00:09:42,978
Despite the chances of the demon dog still being there.

135
00:09:42,978 --> 00:09:45,778
Yes, but we were worried about Hachi!

136
00:09:45,778 --> 00:09:48,278
We thought the demon dog might eat him.

137
00:09:48,278 --> 00:09:51,778
I've figured out how the demon dog got inside.

138
00:09:53,178 --> 00:09:55,078
The backdoor!

139
00:09:55,078 --> 00:09:58,178
The door was unlocked and opened,

140
00:09:58,178 --> 00:10:00,878
